From:    Charles Blaquiere <blaq@io.org>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> From: Dan.Maclean <MACLEDJ@pmitao.usa.com>
> 
> The main problem is that objects don't get "brighter" when the get closer
> to the camera.  They just get bigger, which really doesn't happen with a
> glow. But it looks good!  It is just really time consuming. 

Here's an idea: when you render the scene with only white discs, have 
you tried using Global Fog, with fog color set to black? This would fade 
your glow primitives the further they are from the camera.

