>So, could anyone that subscribes to (or regularly buys) "Computer Artist", 
>"Computer Graphics World" or the new one "3D Design" please post a small 
>review on the respective magazine. Like this:
>

>*---------------------------------------------------------------*
>|   Conny Joensson   |   Swedish Space Corp. Esrange            |
>|   Kiruna           |   Satellite operations - Telecom Div.    |
>|   Sweden           |   cjo@smtpgw.esrange.ssc.se              |
>*---------------------------------------------------------------*
>

I recently let my subscription to "Computer Artist" run out... It seemed to 
focus primarily on 2D work for print, basically Mac and PC, with something 
of a Mac emphasis (due I guess to Mac dominance in print work).  
Occasionally has some good tips on things like retouching or compositing in 
PhotoShop, or scanning real-world objects, etc., but since I don't do much 
print work I didn't find a lot of it that useful.

John. 


