@node IML-61 " MSG-61  Subject: VistaPro upgrades
@toc contents

Subject: VistaPro upgrades
Date:    Friday, 03 November 1995 02:59:18 
From:    Kevin Alvarado <kra@Rocky.aesthetic.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

I've recently received a lot of mail form this mailing list, regarding a
previous post I made regarding my upgrading to the current version of VistaPro.

The most recient version that I'm aware of is VistaPro 3.05 for the Amiga
I recently upgraded from VistaPro 2.01.

I skiped version 3.0 because it was made for AGA Amigas (A1200 & A4000), I have
a trusty A2000 and it wouldn't work with the EGS chip set.  VistaPro 3.05 has
been revised to run nearly flawlessly (I can still find creative ways to crash
it. :)  ) on previous versions of the Amiga chip sets.

Eventualy I will get an A4000... but that is a different story.

-KV-



