>I found a simple solution to the axis position problem, if you can live 
>with one little flaw. Let's say your single blade of grass has its base 
>at Z=0, and stretches 100 units tall. Just move the bottom points to 
>Z=-100 before replicating, slicing, and ungrouping; the resulting 
>objects should have their individual axes around Z=0, perfect for swaying.
>

