@node IML-309 " MSG-309  Subject: Re: Textures
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Textures
Date:    Saturday, 11 November 1995 18:20:49 
From:    Roger Straub <straub@csn.net>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Just to be sure, check that the Mix/Morph value of the texture is set to 
1.00. Sometimes the most obvious and boneheaded solution is the one most 
likely to be overlooked.

Also, the axes of a texture work differently than the axes of a brush. 
The brush's axes tell Imagine where to map it, how deep to make bumps, 
etc. A texture's axes tell Imagine different things depending on the 
texture. Usually it will tell the orientation of a texture, if applicable 
(e.g., the Dots texture will apply just about the same no matter where 
it's pointed) and size of details; bricks, plates, dots, etc. It will 
have no effect whatsoever on the volume the texture is applied to, except 
for a few; Blast is one. Most textures apply themselves over the whole 
surface of the object.

See ya,
   Roger
* Windows'95 = Macintosh'89 = Amiga'85 *

