@node IML-331 " MSG-331  Subject: RE: Red Channel
@toc contents

Subject: RE: Red Channel
Date:    Sunday, 12 November 1995 16:28:45 
From:    jbk4@email.psu.edu (The Prophet)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

You still use your full colour or greyscale maps for

  Colour
  Reflect
  Filter
  Specular
  Ambient
  Environment

mappings.  You can use full colour brushes for

  Altitude
  Hardness
  Roughness
  Fog
  Shiny
  Bright
  R.Index

mappings but Imagine will ignore the blue & green in
those brushs.  Imagine only looks at the red values.
If you are using greyscale maps, it doesn't matter
because the red, blue, & green for each pixel is equal.

I wish Imagine would rescale brushmaps used as backdrops
to fit differing resolutions.  


Jaeson K.
