@node IML-440 " MSG-440  Subject: Re: PC anim playback
@toc contents

Subject: Re: PC anim playback
Date:    Friday, 17 November 1995 14:42:33 
From:    Valleyview@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

If I understand you correctly:

Imagine has two ways of showing the .flc you just made - hit the "play"
button on the project screen - or use "show flic" from the project menu.
There seems to be a difference in the two. The "play" button runs the .flc
from disk, while the "show flic" loads the file into memory which eliminates
the hard disk chatter and choppiness. This will also cause the .flc to run
faster.

Rick

                       @{"           Thread          428" link IML-428}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


