@node IML-539 " MSG-539  Subject: Re: Anybody know how to fix bad chunk size, etc.
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Anybody know how to fix bad chunk size, etc.
Date:    Tuesday, 21 November 1995 09:34:20 
From:    Ted Stethem <tstethem@linknet.kitsap.lib.wa.us>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Imagine has an undocumented limit to the number of edges allowed for an 
object which results in the bad chunk size error message. Same for 
vertices. Lightwave allows for more edges and vertices. If you have an 
object converter like PixelPro or Interchange, they have some limited 
capability for point and vertex reduction. You can also try to save out 
pieces and group them in Imagine.

                       @{"           Thread          588" link IML-588}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


