@node IML-558 " MSG-558  Subject: It seems that I've found a viable solution for Blobs with Stat
@toc contents

Subject: It seems that I've found a viable solution for Blobs with Stat
Date:    Tuesday, 21 November 1995 15:11:19 
From:    Claude GIROLET <Claude_Girolet@msn.com>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

SUBJECT too long. Original SUBJECT is 'It seems that I've found a viable solutio
n for Blobs with States'

----------------------  Original Message Follows  ----------------------

For those, like me who missed the last week discussions about using 4.0 blobs 
with states.

It seems that when you're blob is ready, create a state and in the state 
requestor, UNCHECK "Shape" and "Face color", then the blobs will work 
properly in stage/action editor (at least it works on my pentium for now)

i hope this will help, have a nice day

