@node IML-590 " MSG-590  Subject: RE:Lens flare effects.
@toc contents

Subject: RE:Lens flare effects.
Date:    Wednesday, 22 November 1995 07:22:57 
From:    jbk4@email.psu.edu (The Prophet)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

>Is there anyway of stretching lens flares to create effects like the warp
>flash off TNG - I tried using an altered plane, but failed miserably.

Try applying the lensflare texture to your plane, then create a DEFAULT
state.  In your texture settings, lock the texture to the DEFAULT state.
Stretch your plane however you like it and create another state, STRETCH
or whatever.  

The texture should stick to the surface & get stretched with it.  Don't
forget to select the texture button when you create your state.

Jaeson K.
