Doug Smith asks:
>What happens when you try to lock a texture to a blobby state ?

As far as I can tell, the blob just moves through the texture space.
Brushes, however, seem to tack pretty well.  On the few simple things
I've done, the brush seems stable at the outer limits of the blob,
with the intermediate parts covered with appropriately stretched
markings.  I've only done color brushes.  I suppose alttitude could
get pretty strange.

Greg Denby

