William Reeves and Ash Brannon from PIXAR came down and gave a talk here at
Disney for a local SIGGRAPH meeting and said in no uncertain terms that there
was NO motion capture used for any of "Toy Story".

They actually used Alias to model the characters and their own in-house custom
animation software to do the animation.

